Hong Kong Bourse 2010 Profit Rises; First Gain Since 2007

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a   a n d   S t a n l e y   J a m e s
-- 
2011-03-02T06:05:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/hong-kong-bourse-2010-profit-rises-first-gain-since-2007-1-.html
  Hong Kong  Exchanges & Clearing Ltd.,
the world’s largest-listed exchange operator by market value,
posted a 7 percent increase in profit last year, the first
annual earnings increase in three years  Net income for the year ended Dec. 31 rose to HK$5.04
billion ($647 million), or HK$4.67 a share, from HK$4.7 billion,
or HK$4.36 a share, a year earlier, the company said in a
statement today. That compares with the average HK$5 billion
estimate of 10 analysts in a Bloomberg News survey.  “Market activity improved in 2010 following the gradual
recovery of the global economy,” Hong Kong Exchanges Chairman
Ronald Arculli said in the statement.  Revenue rose 8 percent last year to HK$7.57 billion, the
statement said. The average daily turnover value on the exchange
was about HK$69 billion, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Hong Kong at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 